2. What is Personal Data, and What kinds of Personal Data does Primis collect and process?
“
Personal Data
” means any information which identifies or can be used to identify a natural person, including, but not limited to, first and last name, phone number, email address, IP address, billing information, etc.
“
Non-Personal Data
” means non-identifiable information, for example we may collect information regarding Users concerning their use of the Websites and Services, such as the scope, frequency, latency, pages accessed, what and when a User views or interacts with content and materials displayed through our Services, device specifications, and other technical information regarding the device used to access the Services, such as model, operating system, etc.
We collect certain information about you and your use of the Websites and Services, including information we collect from you directly (
e.g.
when you contact us directly we will collect your contact details) and information we collect about you from others (
e.g.
